&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a high-agency Senior Account Executive with deep domain expertise in Defense and National Security to lead our growth efforts within the Intelligence Community and Department of Defense. This is a mission-critical role focused on capturing immediate pipeline, securing key renewals, and architecting long-term outreach strategies for our most sensitive accounts. You will act as a strategic quarterback, navigating complex procurement vehicles and building deep trust with government stakeholders to deliver Sayari’s world-class risk intelligence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and execute the full sales lifecycle from prospecting to close for National Security and Defense accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and lead a multi-threaded outreach strategy into new sub-verticals within the IC and DoD.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Managing Director to set strategic priorities and accounts while maintaining complete ownership of the execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure 100% retention of existing high-value accounts by managing renewal bandwidth and identifying expansion opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, accurate, and updated pipeline in Salesforce, providing regular strategic updates to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with Solutions, Legal, and Government Affairs to navigate complex federal procurement and technical requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a self-starter who identifies market gaps and proactively builds the &quot;Sayari way&quot; within your territory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SKILLS &amp;amp; EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active TS/SCI security clearance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in federal sales, specifically selling complex software or data solutions into the National Security or Defense sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of meeting or exceeding $2M+ annual quotas in the federal space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep literacy in federal procurement cycles, contract vehicles, and agency-specific nuances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
